*This project has been created as part of the 42 curriculum by mafzal | mgolasze*

## Description
This project implements a custom Unix-like shell (`minishell`) as part of the 42 curriculum.
It recreates core Bash behavior for command parsing and execution, including pipes, redirections,
heredoc, environment expansion, logical operators, and builtins.

## Instructions
### Compilation
From the project root:

```bash
make
```

Clean rebuild:

```bash
make re
```

Full clean:

```bash
make fclean
```

### Execution
Run the shell with:

```bash
./minishell
```

### Useful checks
Strict Valgrind check for real leaks:

```bash
valgrind --leak-check=full --show-leak-kinds=definite,indirect,possible --errors-for-leak-kinds=definite,indirect,possible --track-origins=yes ./minishell
```

